This adds a compose key (shift + right ctrl key) to a US qwerty keyboard layout (see chrome://settings/languages; Compose Key in English (US))

See the following link for a list of the supported combinations:
 http://www.hermit.org/Linux/ComposeKeys.html

How to use:
 - press shift and right ctrl key
 - release
 - type a combination
 - if there is a match the conversion will happen automatically otherwise you get what you typed